- upgrade to Keen Javascript API 3.4.0
- upgrade to bootstrap 3.3.6
- upgrade to jQuery 1.12.0
- [trends] issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#38 : Add 'days without fail' metric
- [trends,stats] issue buildtimetrend/python-dashboard#3 : Show spinner when charts are being updated
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#146 : improve constructing badgeUrl

v0.3 (released on 16Nov2015)
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#21 : add charts with build job results
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#52 : upgrade to Keen JS API 3.2
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#23 : add charts with build job results grouped by branch or by build environment parameters
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#70 : use bootstrap buttons and ButtonClass on dashboard to select timeframe
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#93 : upgrade to bootstrap 3.3.5
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#88 : use caching for Keen.io charts
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#99 : Enable auto refreshing dashboard charts with `refresh` url parameter
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#108 : Make projects menu scrollable
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#100, #103 : Filter on build properties for chart data, like build
trigger, branch, build matrix, build result
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#108 : Limit size of projects dropdown menu and make it scrollable
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#91 : display stats of pull requests
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#45 : add charts with average build job per branch and build matrix parameters
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#113 : use url parameter to set default timeframe
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#121 : use url parameter to set query filters
- upgrade to Keen Javascript API 3.3.0
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#84 : Add admin dashboard with service usage statistics

v0.2 (released on 18Feb2015)
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#19 : update Keen.io charts using query request refresh function
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#26 : add chart displaying builds per time of day or day of week
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#44 : Display buildtime averages of different timeframes in the same chart
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#15 : use Keen.io dashboard template for trends dashboard
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#58 : split project in a client
(https://github.com/buildtimetrend/python-client), library
(https://github.com/buildtimetrend/buildtimetrend/python-lib) and dashboard (current project)
- rename 'trends' folder to 'dashboard'
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#17 : add parameterized (repo name, interval) build status badge to dashboard
- issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#18 : link to project website and project repo on dashboard
- run queries in GMT timezone
- schema change : save build job data in build_jobs.job (was builds.build)

before v0.2, dashboard was part of the Buildtime Trend client repo. A seperate
repo was created for the dashboard, see issue buildtimetrend/python-lib#58
